    "description": "<p>When you are hit by an attack from a creature you can see within 120 feet, you can use your reaction to make a melee or ranged spell attack against the creature. On a hit, the creature takes 1d6 force damage, and you gain an equal amount of exertion point. The amount of exertion points gained this way increases by 1 when you reach 11th level, and again at 15th level.</p>\n<p>When you use this feature, you can't cast spells other than cantrips until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<p>When you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p>",
